{
  "texts": [
    "We compute precision (P), recall (R), F1-score (F1), prediction count (#PD), and ground truth count (#GT) at both chunk and paper levels.",
    "Paperlevel results are in Appendix A.6.",
    "We evaluate the proposed method using multiple backbone models to assess performance variations.",
    "We also include generalist NER baselines, GLiNER (Zaratiana et al., 2024) and NuNER (Bogdanov et al., 2024), which rely solely on text input and label names.",
    "This setup isolates the effects of model architecture, parameter count, and domain specialization under identical taxonomy constraints and RAG configurations across experiments."
  ]
}